Ecological notes : common in all types of woodland; calcareous grassland; wetlands including fen, bog, raised mire, lake and wildfowl reserve, water meadows with hedges and gravel pits; parkland; garden; sand dunes. Reared from nests of moles (several rearings), common shrew, red squirrel, rabbit and from old wasp’s nest. ii–xi.
